  "aiHints": {
    "analysisContext": "Raw H.264 Annex B byte-stream. NALU sequence: start code (3 or 4 bytes: 000001 or 00000001) + NALU header (1B) + RBSP data. Typical stream start: SPS (type 7) + PPS (type 8) + IDR (type 5). SPS layout (after header): profile_idc(1B) + constraint_set_flags(1B) + level_idc(1B) + seq_parameter_set_id(UVLC) + ... + pic_width/height_in_mbs_minus1 (UVLC). profile_idc: 66=Baseline, 77=Main, 100=High, 110=High10, 122=High422, 244=High444. level_idc: 30=L3.0, 40=L4.0, 51=L5.1. H.264 in MP4 uses avcC (length-prefixed, not Annex B).",
    "suggestedInspections": [
      "Verify 0x00 0x00 0x00 0x01 at offset 0 — Annex B long start code",
      "Check NALU type at offset 4 bits 4-0: 7=SPS (first in stream), 8=PPS, 5=IDR",
      "If NALU type is 7 (SPS): byte 5 = profile_idc (66=Baseline, 77=Main, 100=High)",
      "byte 7 = level_idc × 10 = level (e.g., 51 = Level 5.1 = 4K@30fps)",
      "Check for emulation prevention bytes (0x000003) in NALU data"
    ]
  },
  "software": [
    "FFmpeg (h264 parser)",
    "VLC media player",
    "x264 encoder",
    "Hardware decoders (Intel QSV, NVENC, AMD VCE)",
    "All modern video players and streaming platforms"
  ],
  "formatRelationships": {
    "category": "Video",
    "extensions": [".h264", ".264", ".avc"],
    "relatedFormats": ["H265", "MP4", "MKV", "TS"],
    "note": "Raw H.264 Annex B elementary stream — typically encapsulated in MPEG-TS (.ts), MP4 (.mp4), MKV (.mkv), or FLV (.flv). In MP4 containers, H.264 uses the length-prefix (AVCC) format instead of Annex B start codes. The Annex B format is used in broadcast/streaming (MPEG-TS) and raw files."
  },
